section.section:
The Maryland Agricultural Land Preservation Foundation shall be governed and administered by a board of trustees composed of the State Treasurer, who shall serve as an ex officio member, the Comptroller, who shall serve as an ex officio member, the Secretary of Planning, who shall serve as an ex officio member, and the Secretary who shall serve as an ex officio member, and nine members from the State at-large to be appointed by the Governor, at least six of whom shall be farmer representatives from different areas of the State. The State Treasurer may appoint, as the Treasurer's designee, a deputy treasurer to serve on the board of trustees. The Secretary of Planning may appoint as the Secretary's designee an individual within the Department of Planning. All of the farmer representatives shall be actively engaged in or retired from active farming. Four of the six farmer representatives shall be appointed as follows:
One from a list of three nominees submitted by the Maryland Agricultural Commission;
One from a list of three nominees submitted by the Maryland Farm Bureau;
One from a list of three nominees submitted by the Maryland State Grange; and
One from a list of three nominees submitted by the Young Farmers Advisory Board.
